network_overview: The capture contains SIP signaling only (IMS signaling plane) for VoLTE/VoNR-related sessions. Multiple INVITE attempts receive provisional responses (100/180/183) and PRACK/UPDATE exchanges, but many sessions are terminated by caller-initiated CANCEL, and some dialogs are later cleared by BYE with vendor/opaque Reason text values.

pattern_matches.pattern_name: Caller cancels call attempt (CANCEL) leading to 487 Request Terminated for INVITE
pattern_matches.spec_reference: RFC 3261 (CANCEL method; INVITE transaction terminated with 487)

Call-ID 1eEeXOyORCYzPJN6BcinNvKt: subsequent SIP 487 Response at 1726068029.304147 and ACK at 1726068029.335153
Call-ID asbc1eEeXOyORCYzPJN6BcinNvKt: SIP CANCEL at 1726068029.306026 with Reason 'SIP;cause=200;text=Call Rejected By User""' followed by SIP 487 Response at 1726068029.319634
pattern_matches.explanation: The SIP signaling shows an INVITE in progress followed by a CANCEL from the caller side, and the INVITE is then terminated with a 487 response, matching standard SIP behavior.

observations.finding: Multiple call attempts are explicitly cancelled by the caller after receiving provisional responses (180/183), indicating user/app-initiated termination rather than a network reject at SIP layer in those instances.
observations.evidence: Example Call-ID 1eEeXOyORCYzPJN6BcinNvKt: INVITE 1726067992.944127 -> 183 1726067995.564286 -> 180 1726067996.735536 -> CANCEL 1726068029.302117 (Reason: SIP;cause=200;text=Call Rejected By User"") -> 487 1726068029.304147

observations.finding: The provided 'media_findings' claim 'No 180/183 response received' for several calls, but the call message lists show 180 and/or 183 responses present; this indicates an inconsistency in the derived findings vs observed SIP message list.

root_causes.description: Several call attempts are terminated by a SIP CANCEL sent by the calling side, with a Reason header indicating 'SIP;cause=200;text=Call Rejected By User""'. The network then responds with 200 OK to the CANCEL and terminates the INVITE transaction with 487, followed by ACK.
root_causes.impact: Call setup is aborted before a final successful call establishment for those attempts; this is consistent with user/app cancellation behavior at the SIP layer.
root_causes.confidence_justification: Direct SIP evidence: CANCEL is observed, followed by expected 200 (CANCEL) and 487 (INVITE) plus ACK within the same Call-ID.
evidence_refs: Call-ID 1eEeXOyORCYzPJN6BcinNvKt: SIP/CANCEL at 1726068029.302117 (Reason: SIP;cause=200;text=Call Rejected By User"")
Call-ID 1eEeXOyORCYzPJN6BcinNvKt: SIP/200 Response to CANCEL at 1726068029.304146

root_causes.issue: Non-standard/opaque call clearing reasons in BYE (vendor-specific)
root_causes.description: Some established dialogs (presence of SIP 200 Response and ACK after INVITE) are later cleared by BYE messages containing Reason strings with values such as 'X.int;reasoncode=0x00000000;add-info=0132.0001.0B2E' or 'SIP;cause=503;text=... PS to CS Handover""'. These are not standard SIP response codes in the BYE itself but rather Reason header content; their semantics cannot be confirmed from this capture alone.
root_causes.impact: Call termination occurs with opaque cause reporting, limiting standardized RCA and making it unclear whether termination was user-triggered, network-triggered, or interworking-related based solely on SIP here.
root_causes.confidence_justification: BYE messages and their Reason text are directly observed; however, the meaning of the Reason text tokens is not provable from the capture without a mapping/vendor definition.
evidence_refs: Call-ID asbcM3hLVREVD5ydTfb0VA0EWIeM: SIP/BYE at 1726069583.069769 (Reason: SIP;cause=503;text=03077... PS to CS Handover"")

inconclusive_aspects.aspect: Whether any SIP-layer network rejection occurred for the cancelled call attempts
inconclusive_aspects.reason: The observed failures for many calls are driven by caller CANCEL; there is no observed SIP final error response (4xx/5xx/6xx) preceding the CANCEL in those dialogs.
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: SIP traces including any upstream/downstream legs (full end-to-end SIP path) to verify if any prior provisional/final responses or internal routing decisions triggered the user/app cancellation.

inconclusive_aspects.aspect: Media (ringback tone, RTP establishment, codec negotiation, audio quality)
inconclusive_aspects.reason: Observation point is IMS signaling only; no RTP/SDP media is detected and codec negotiation is reported as absent.
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: User-plane/media capture (RTP/RTCP) and SIP bodies containing SDP at a point where SDP is visible to confirm early media/ringback behavior and media path establishment.

inconclusive_aspects.aspect: Meaning of 'X.int;reasoncode=0x00000000;add-info=0132.0001.0B2E' and other opaque Reason text values
inconclusive_aspects.reason: The Reason text is vendor/proprietary/opaque; no standard mapping is provided in the evidence.
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Vendor mapping/overlay for these Reason header formats or correlated system logs from the SIP elements generating the BYE.

inconclusive_aspects.reason: Call message lists show 180/183 responses present for example calls, contradicting the media_findings flags.
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Raw SIP message capture (full payloads) or corrected analytics output to validate whether 180/183 were actually received on the relevant leg and whether they contained SDP/early media indicators.

recommendations.action: Validate analytics pipeline producing 'media_findings' (ringback/no provisional) against the actual SIP message list and raw packets; correct any leg-selection or parsing logic errors.
recommendations.rationale: The evidence contains 180/183 responses, yet the findings claim none; resolving this discrepancy is necessary before any ringback-related RCA can be trusted.

recommendations.action: For recurring CANCEL scenarios, correlate SIP CANCEL timestamps with client/app UI actions and device logs to confirm user/app-driven call abandonment vs upstream signaling triggers.
recommendations.rationale: CANCEL with Reason 'Call Rejected By User' is directly observed; confirming the initiating factor requires endpoint-side correlation not present in this capture.

recommendations.action: Obtain vendor documentation for BYE Reason formats (e.g., 'X.int;reasoncode=0x00000000;add-info=...') and establish a standardized mapping in reporting.
recommendations.rationale: BYE includes opaque Reason tokens; without a mapping, root-cause attribution is limited even though the signaling event is visible.

session_analysis.signaling_health: SIP signaling exchanges (INVITE with 100/180/183, PRACK, UPDATE, and subsequent CANCEL/487 or BYE/200) are present and generally coherent at the transaction level; however, many call attempts end via caller CANCEL and some call clears include opaque Reason strings that cannot be interpreted from this capture alone.
session_analysis.user_plane_health: Not observable at this capture point (IMS signaling only; no user-plane protocols captured).
session_analysis.voice_quality: Not observable at this capture point (no RTP/RTCP captured; no SDP media detected).
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: Not possible from this capture because only SIP signaling is present and no media/user-plane telemetry is available.
